In Scala,
 we achieve "Safe Levels" through 
\backslash
textbf{Type-Level Domain Modeling}.
 Instead of the runtime checking a "taint flag" on a string,
 the compiler ensures that untrusted data is wrapped in a type that the rest of the system refuses to touch.
