subsection*{Implicit Safety:
 The "Taint" of Options}
\end_layout

\begin_layout Plain Layout

The closest spiritual successor to Ruby's "Safe Levels" in Scala is how we handle 
\backslash
texttt{null}.
 In Ruby,
 calling a method on 
\backslash
texttt{nil} causes a crash.
 In Scala's 
\backslash
textbf{Strict Nulls} mode (Chapter 23),
 the compiler "taints" any value that could be null by forcing it into a 
\backslash
texttt{String | Null} union type.
\end_layout

